comments.text:
Eh... I can relate. I smoked a decent amount of weed throughout high 
school, stopped almost entirely for two years, then one day decided to 
smoke a joint with my brother because why the fuck not, he said it was 
awesome shit. A couple of minutes after we smoked it the high started to 
kick in and I thought it was pretty awesome... then I walked into the 
kitchen to grab some water and that's when shit hit the fan - BAD. I fell 
to the ground and my heart started pounding at a million miles a minute. 
After laying down on the floor for a bit I said to myself "I can't let 
anyone see me like this" so I used all my strength to get up and lay in 
down.

The next two hours would be the longest hours of my life as I ACTUALLY 
thought I was going to die. My heart was pounding, I was breathing very 
intensely, I couldn't form a sentence (was mumbling to myself pretty much 
the entire time), I felt extreme paranoia and anxiety, shaking, sweating, 
etc. Tried to throw on some headphones to pass the time but the second they 
started playing my head felt like it was going to explode, so I chucked 
them across the room without hesitation. And when the high/trip was finally 
over, I sat there for about 20 minutes in complete shock about what just 
happened, and said to myself I would never touch that shit again. A year 
and a half later, I haven't touched weed again.

I know I didn't green out because I wasn't seeing doubles or having spins 
and I didn't feel like puking once, it was just... I don't know, one of the 
worst trips of my life. I've done a fair mount of other shit like M, K, 
blow, percocets, and shrooms and I swear man, never experienced anything 
like I did that night.﻿
